content.text:
The issue was that `FunctionSignatureRule` inserted the missing whitespace before the function body in the wrong place in the AST. Specifically, it was inserting the whitespace after the closing parenthesis of the parameter list, which effectively made the whitespace a child of `VALUE_PARAMETER_LIST` instead of a sibling of the `BLOCK` (and child of the `FUN` element). This caused other rules (like `FunctionStartOfBodySpacingRule`) to fail to see the whitespace in the expected position (as a preceding sibling of the block), leading to repeated violations and failure to resolve all errors.

The fix involves modifying `FunctionSignatureRule.kt` to explicitly check if the body is a `BLOCK` and, if so, insert the whitespace as a child of the parent element (the function) immediately before the block, ensuring the correct AST structure.

